# Serial recording started at: Sun Jun 08 12:00:00 2026
# Format: [timestamp_ms] direction byte|byte|byte|...
# Direction: R=read (from device), W=write (to device)
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sample synthetic-but-realistic captured RS-485 session for end-to-end tests.
#
# Contents: an AquaRite salt-water generator (SWG, device id 0x50) identifying
# itself and reporting status, which populates a chlorinator in the DataHub:
#   * AQUARITE_GetId  (0x14) : Master -> SWG identification query.
#   * AQUARITE_Percent(0x11) : generating level = 40%.
#   * AQUARITE_PPM    (0x16) : salt concentration = 3200 PPM, status On.
#
# The R lines are the bytes that arrived FROM the bus (the replay input).  The
# single W line below is the application's own past output captured during
# recording and MUST be ignored on replay (it is here on purpose to prove the
# replayer/LoadFixture skip W-direction bytes).
#
# Frames are fully framed + checksummed exactly as MessageBuilder produces them;
# the e2e test cross-checks these bytes against MessageBuilder so a drift fails.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
[         0] # Opened device: /dev/ttyUSB0
[       100] W 0x10|0x02|0x50|0x14|0x76|0x10|0x03
[       142] R 0x10|0x02|0x50|0x14|0x76|0x10|0x03
[       310] R 0x10|0x02|0x50|0x11|0x28|0x9b|0x10|0x03
[       512] R 0x10|0x02|0x00|0x16|0x20|0x00|0x48|0x10|0x03
# Recording ended
